===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Shuowen: {{Han compound|酋|t1=wine|寸|t2=hand|ls=ic}} – a hand {{zh-l|寸}} offering a vessel of wine {{zh-l|酋}} to show respect and veneration.

However, based on the small seal script, it may instead be a variant of {{zh-l|𢍜}}, which is {{Han compound|酋|t1=wine|廾|t2=two hands|ls=ic}}.

===Etymology===
Cognate to {{cog|bo|བཙུན}}, {{m|bo|བཙུན་པ|t=respectable, venerable}}, {{m|bo|མཚུན|t=ancestor god}}. The "vessel" sense is because it was used in ritual ceremonies ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

; "glorious; marvelous; wonderful"
